{"comment": "The generated test cases cover all branches of the recursive palindrome function, including the base cases (empty span and single-element span), the recursive case (elements match), and the mismatch case (elements do not match). I have used std::vector to provide the underlying storage for the std::span argument.", "tests": ["palindromev(std::vector<List>{})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<0>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<0>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<2>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<0>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<2>}, List{std::in_place_index<0>}})", "palindromev(std::vector<List>{List{std::in_place_index<0>}, List{std::in_place_index<1>}, List{std::in_place_index<2>}, List{std::in_place_index<3>}, List{std::in_place_index<4>}})"]}
